# üöÄ feature request

### Relevant Package
@angular/service-worker
@angular/pwa


### Description
At the moment there is no support for [cache.match options](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Cache/match)  in listed above package. I have a scenario with images which have some dynamic hashes as url parameters. 

### Desired behaviour 
The same image 

- https://cdn.example.com/image1.png?foo=bar1
- https://cdn.example.com/image1.png?foo=bar2
- https://cdn.example.com/image1.png?foo=bar3

to be cached as 

- https://cdn.example.com/image1.png

### Describe the solution you'd like
It's good to have possibility to specify some properties in ngsw-config.json assetGroup like
```
interface AssetGroup {
  name: string;
  installMode?: 'prefetch' | 'lazy';
  ...  
  cacheOptions?: {
    ignoreSearch?: boolean;
    ignoreMethod?: boolean;
    ignoreVary?: boolean;
  };
  ...
}

```

Users outside of Google don't usually need closure annotations.

We should also follow up with ng-packagr so that tsickle is not required as a peerDependency and afterwards, we be able to remove tsickle as a dependency when generating.

//cc @alexeagle and @vikerman

**Versions**
Angular 7

**Observed behavior**
modules are not getting excluded while building

**Desired behavior**
Is there any way to exclude few modules while building the app...?

**Mention any other details that might be useful (optional)**
I tried to conditionally import basic and advanced module, but still I am getting Basic and Advanced module code in the main.js. 

